This linkedin post from Gary Marcus<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://www=
.linkedin.com/posts/gary-marcus-b6384b4_why-is-the-ai-backlash-growing-outs=
ide-share-7456554051284021248-qefz?utm_source=3Dshare&utm_medium=3Dmember_d=
esktop&rcm=3DACoAAAbpgc4BRAQmkOWfG4QzZjocR0kV4pimVOs__;!!LIr3w8kk_Xxm!vW0Wl=
nhFW__klHllVhGTSMn5IBM60A8NZ-ZRAva3JldINfTkRLYjnDGN8L1daw1o4b43vFcymV7ls3b3=
$ > I found interesting because of this comment:

Outside of coding (where there is clear value), and a handful of other doma=
ins (e.g. brainstorming), Generative AI has been a net negative for society.

Our wiki kinda allows us to "brainstorming".

________________________________
From: Sumit Gulwani <sumitg@microsoft.com>
Sent: Saturday, May 2, 2026 11:38 PM
To: Sadra Sabouri Halestani <sabourih@usc.edu>
Subject: Presentation

I looked at the movies that you shared. Looks like you already had the idea=
 of "presentation" using the wiki.

